danny-avila/LibreChat#12429.body:
### What happened?

When using Mistral models (e.g. mistral-large-3) deployed via Azure AI Foundry as an Agent with tools, the API returns error 400 after a tool execution:
{"object":"Error","message":"Unexpected role 'user' after role 'tool'","type":"invalid_request_message_order","code":3230}


LibreChat should ensure that ToolMessage is never directly followed by HumanMessage in the payload sent to Mistral-compatible APIs.

In @librechat/agents/src/graphs/Graph.ts, in the callModel function, just before invoking model.stream(), scan finalMessages and insert a bridge AIMessage between any ToolMessage → HumanMessage sequence:


// Fix strict message ordering for providers that reject user after tool (e.g. Mistral)
const patched: BaseMessage[] = [];
for (let i = 0; i < finalMessages.length; i++) {
  patched.push(finalMessages[i]);
  const curr = finalMessages[i];
  const next = finalMessages[i + 1];
  const isCurrTool = curr instanceof ToolMessage || ('role' in curr && (curr as any).role === 'tool');
  const isNextHuman = next && (next instanceof HumanMessage || ('role' in next && (next as any).role === 'user'));
  if (isCurrTool && isNextHuman) {
    patched.push(new AIMessage({ content: 'Understood.' }));
  }
}
finalMessages = patched;
Alternatively, this could be scoped to specific providers if a broader fix is not desired.

